      "writtenOn": "2021-02-23T15:38:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "https://source.chromium.org/search?q\u003d%22%5E%5Cs*(%5B%5Cw-%5D%2B):%20*(.*)$%22\u0026ss\u003dchromium\n\nTools that interact with Gerrit deal with footers that I thought were a subset of git trailers, so I expected something in the go/gerrit library vs something in the go/git library, because we wanted this for our communications with Gerrit. But calling trailers from go/git in a way that is supported by Gerrit makes sense as well.\n\n(might be useful to post a comment for where you got `(.+): (.+)` from)",
      "parentUuid": "c9f9805a_410ffc80",
      "revId": "04a767522195053054de61818628c6b29a5c238a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
